  "instructions": [
    "In a small bowl whisk together mustard powder, lime juice, fish sauce, ground ginger, and chili flakes to make a thin glaze.",
    "Warm each tortilla over a dry skillet for 15 seconds to make it pliable.",
    "Spread a thin layer of the glaze on one side of the tortilla.",
    "Evenly distribute shredded chicken, corn kernels, diced bell pepper, shredded carrot, and diced green onion over the glazed side.",
    "Fold the tortilla over to enclose the filling, forming a half-moon shape.",
    "Heat coconut oil in a nonstick skillet over medium heat and place the quesadilla seam side down.",
    "Cook 3-4 minutes until golden brown and crispy, flip, and cook the other side for an additional 2-3 minutes.",
    "Remove from skillet, let rest 30 seconds, cut into wedges, and garnish with fresh cilantro before serving."
  ],
